The celebrated cardinal Polignac, in his poem, entitled Anti-Lucretius, long after his death, has given a very extraordinary account of an animal, which he calls a Polish animal, and named Baubax. He says, that these animals are of two kinds, some black and some of a yellowish red; thatthese two kinds keep separate, and make war upon each other, drawing up in large bodies, and encamping like opposite armies ; that they engage, and fight desperately ; and that the victors, whether the blackor the red, take and carry away as many prisoners as they can ; and retaining them in captivity, employthem in domestic drudgery, and other slavish business; so that all the red which are found among the black, and all the black that arefound among the red, are in a state of the most abject servitude.
